  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>These will be short notes on the <fr:link href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NJ72iEPRXFk" type="external">video tutorial</fr:link> by <fr:link href="/sanjayshakkottai/" title="Sanjay Shakkottai" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/sanjayshakkottai/" display-uri="sanjayshakkottai" type="local">Sanjay Shakkottai</fr:link>. </html:p>
  <fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/kellenkanarios/" title="Kellen Kanarios" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/kellenkanarios/" display-uri="kellenkanarios" type="local">Kellen Kanarios</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>1</fr:day></fr:date><fr:title text="What is an SDE?">What is an SDE?</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>
  First we have to discuss ODEs. For the ODE,
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[dx_t = \underbrace {\mu (x_t, t)}_{\text {``drift term''}} \mathrm {d}t]]></fr:tex>
  We have the following possible vector representation
  </html:p>

  <fr:resource hash="9ef27f3f739867d1018a82994571e304"><fr:resource-content><html:img src="https://kellenkanarios.com/9ef27f3f739867d1018a82994571e304.svg" /></fr:resource-content><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[
